    <section>
        <title>Lunar Theory</title>
        <section>
            <title>Chapter 14</title>
            <section>
                <title>Law 1</title>
                <para>
                    The moon has two mean movements.
                    The moon itself rotates on a small circle that does not surround all of the Earth.
                    Moon's movement on that small circle is called mean
                    lunar anomaly (אמצע המסלול).
                    The small circle (epicycle) itself rotates on a big circle (deferent) that surrounds the Earth.
                    The mean movement of the small circle on the big circle that surrounds the Earth is called
                    mean lunar longitude (אמצע הירח).
                </para>
            </section>
