            <section>
                <title>Law 6</title>
                <para>
                    The value of mean [lunar longitude] after you add to it or subtract from it or leave it as 
                    it is - that is mean lunar longitude approximately a third of an hour after sunset on the
                    date you are calculating it for. And this is what is called 'mean lunar longitude during observation time'.
                </para>
            </section>
